text.tspan: To get software updates, this system needs to be registered with Red Hat, either
using the Red Hat Customer Portal or a local subscription server.
Ideal: In-page popup. (Tricky to implement? Needs cross-module support in Cockpit.)
Least work: Switch to subscription page without hand-holiding.

flowRoot.flowPara: Sadly, the person using Cockpit would have to figure out that they have to get back to software updates to continue.
It could be worse: At least there was a link from the updates page, right?
It would be great if there were some additional next-step here to get back to software updates. It would require modifications to the subscription page.
It could be as simple as adding a one-time message with a link back to software updates.
Registration Page, immediately with Registration Dialog
